@model CommunityHub.Forms.Steps.PromoteFormModel
@*
    Fields-ONLY partial for the Promote step (REQUIREMENTS §148 / §116).
    Contains NO <form>, no toggle button, no page chrome (h1/card), no Back-to-hub link —
    the HOST (the standalone /Speaker/Promote page OR the generic /Forms/Wizard shell) owns
    those and places this partial inside its single form. Mobile-first. Promote has no
    editable inputs (it is a MANUAL "mark done" step), so this is purely informational.
    Bound to CommunityHub.Forms.Steps.PromoteFormModel.
*@

<p>Help us spread the word! Promote your session(s) on LinkedIn and tag
   <strong>@CommunityHub.Forms.Steps.PromoteFormModel.Hashtags</strong>.</p>

@if (Model.Done)
{
    <p class="success" role="status">✅ You've marked this step complete. Thank you!</p>
}

<p>The best way is to publish your released session graphic straight from your
   <a asp-page="/Speaker/Graphics">SoMe graphics page</a> — it builds a LinkedIn
   draft (and can publish to the event's LinkedIn page) with the correct tags.</p>

<div style="display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:10px;margin:16px 0;">
    <a asp-page="/Speaker/Graphics" class="btn-primary" style="text-align:center;">Open my SoMe graphics &amp; publish</a>
    <a href="@Model.LinkedInShareUrl" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="btn-primary" style="text-align:center;">Share on LinkedIn</a>
</div>

<p style="font-size:13px;color:#6b7280;">
    Note: a prefilled LinkedIn share can only carry the link; add your own words
    and the tags @CommunityHub.Forms.Steps.PromoteFormModel.Hashtags. For a graphic +
    generated post text, use the SoMe graphics page above.
</p>
